Nara is 35 kilometers south of Kyoto City and about 28 kilometers east of Osaka. Thus, it’s within easy day trip distances of these cities. Of course, if you want to slow down and enjoy Nara a bit more, it makes sense to stay a night in Nara to really explore the area.
This ancient city is home to three World Heritage sites, comprising Historic Monuments of Ancient Nara, Buddhist Monuments in the Horyuji Area, and Sacred Sites and Pilgrimage Routes in the Kii Mountain Range. #japan #narapark #cute #deer #travel

How much is the entrance fee to Arashiyama Monkey Park Iwatayama?
Iwatayama Monkey Park

The entrance fee is 550 yen, and requires walking up a big hill, so be prepared for that if you have some issue with hills. The path up through the Monkey Park isn’t too steep, and a few places offer nice views of the scenery. #monkeys #animals #cute #japan #travel

Transport yourself to a world of exquisite flavors and timeless elegance with the legendary 1981 Château Trotakoy Pomerol. 🌟🍇✨ This extraordinary vintage showcases the remarkable artistry of winemaking, capturing the essence of a bygone era.

🔍 Deep Dive into the Past: Aged to Perfection 🔎

Step into the enchanting world of 1981, where every sip tells a story. 📚✨ Aged to perfection, this Pomerol gem boasts a rich bouquet of flavors, seamlessly intertwining notes of dark berries, velvety tannins, and a touch of earthiness. Its harmonious balance and complex layers are a testament to the expertise of the winemakers who crafted it.
